WEBVTT

00:01:57.252 --> 00:02:00.458
SMV: Jordan Reed touchdown
in a four-by-one individual iso slant.

00:02:00.482 --> 00:02:02.434
Reporter 2: Check out the brain on Sean.

00:02:02.458 --> 00:02:03.926
Reporter 1: You're amazing.

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:06.950
AG: He even remembers plays
going back 16 years,

00:02:06.974 --> 00:02:09.622
when he was in the state semifinals

00:02:09.646 --> 00:02:10.797
in high school.

00:02:11.885 --> 00:02:15.337
This kind of recall gives him
a big edge as a coach.

00:02:15.361 --> 00:02:18.442
When he needs to make a quick decision
with the game on the line,

00:02:18.466 --> 00:02:22.783
he has an entire library of successes
and mistakes at his fingertips.

00:02:23.458 --> 00:02:25.950
Sean McVay is clearly a savant.

00:02:26.529 --> 00:02:29.129
But memory is not just an innate talent.

00:02:29.530 --> 00:02:31.950
You can strengthen yours, like a muscle.